"title": "5534: sleep, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5534",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture often uses sleep as an image of spiritual laziness or a lack of alertness towards God.</p>\n<h2>Sleep as an image of spiritual laziness</h2>\n<h3>Lack of watchfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:10\">ISA 56:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:43-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:43–24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:39-Luke12:40\">LUK 12:39–12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:35-Mark13:36\">MRK 13:35–13:36</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual dullness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:25-Acts28:27\">ACT 28:25–28:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:9–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:34-Prov23:35\">PRO 23:34–23:35</a>ROM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:8\">11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:10\">ISA 29:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's call to awake from sleep</h2>\n<h3>The need to arise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:11-Rom13:12\">ROM 13:11–13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:17\">ISA 51:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:1\">ISA 52:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:1\">ISA 60:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:14\">EPH 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:2\">REV 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>The command to be alert</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:15\">REV 16:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:41\">MAT 26:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32-Mark13:34\">MRK 13:32–13:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:35\">LUK 12:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:18\">EPH 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:6-1Thess5:8\">1TH 5:6–5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8\">1PE 5:8</a></p>\n<h3>The plea for revival</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:18\">PSA 80:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps85:6\">PSA 85:6</a></p>\n<h2>The image of God awaking from sleep</h2>\n<h3>From his past judgments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:65\">PSA 78:65</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Prayers for God to rise up against his enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:6\">PSA 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:23\">PSA 35:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:23-Ps44:24\">PSA 44:23–44:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:20\">PSA 73:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:1-Ps80:2\">PSA 80:1–80:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:9\">ISA 51:9</a></p>\n<h2>The contrast between God who never sleeps and false gods</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:3-Ps121:4\">PSA 121:3–121:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:27\">1KI 18:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:19\">HAB 2:19</a></p>",
